Reasoning: The paper deals with channel coding and error probabilities, which are topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of the information spectrum method and the analysis of the tradeoff between code rate and error probabilities also suggest a possible fit with the Coding and Information Theory (cs.CC) sub-category. The study of asymptotic regimes and the use of cumulant generating functions may also indicate a connection with the Statistical Theory (cs.ST) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of additive channels and uniform input distribution could suggest a link with the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
